The paper proposes a new class of global string kernels that aim to discover global properties hidden in the strings through global alignments. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions that existing string kernels have been used in areas such as bioinformatics, text, and audio mining, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), or Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.CL.
